│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                  │
│                                                              │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------              │
│ 1. **Understanding the Issue**: The assertion failure occurs │
│ because the VPlan cost model and the legacy cost model       │
│ disagree on the vectorization factor (VF). This disagreement │
│ arises when the VPlan contains additional simplifications    │
│ that are not accounted for in the legacy cost model.         │
│                                                              │
│ 2. **Analyzing `opt`'s Log**: The log indicates that the     │
│ assertion failure is triggered in `computeBestVF` when       │
│ comparing `BestFactor.Width` and `LegacyVF.Width`. The       │
│ function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` is used to  │
│ check if the VPlan has extra simplifications, but it fails   │
│ to resolve due to missing or incorrect handling of certain   │
│ instructions.                                                │
│                                                              │
│ 3. **Root Cause Analysis**: The function                     │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` does not correctly   │
│ identify all instructions that are part of the VPlan or      │
│ skipped for cost computation. This leads to a false          │
│ negative, causing the assertion to fail even when the VPlan  │
│ legitimately contains additional simplifications.            │
│                                                              │
│ 4. **Proposed Edit Points**:                                 │
│    - **Edit Point 1**: Modify                                │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` to ensure it         │
│ accurately identifies all relevant instructions. This        │
│ involves refining the logic to include all instructions that │
│ are part of the VPlan or explicitly skipped for cost         │
│ computation.                                                 │
│    - **Edit Point 2**: Update the assertion in               │
│ `computeBestVF` to handle cases where the VPlan legitimately │
│ contains additional simplifications. This may involve adding │
│ more robust checks or logging to better understand the       │
│ disagreement.                                                │
│                                                              │
│ 5. **Conclusion**: The proposed edits aim to fix the logic   │
│ in `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` and improve the   │
│ assertion in `computeBestVF`. These changes will ensure that │
│ the VPlan cost model and legacy cost model can coexist       │
│ without triggering false assertion failures.                 │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------              │
